---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
---

<Layout title="About | Artifact Studio">
  <section class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 py-20">
    <h1 class="text-5xl font-header font-black leading-relaxed">About.</h1>
    <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-x-10">
      <p class="mt-4  text-stone-500 font-body leading-relaxed">
        Artifact Studio is an owner-operated studio based in the heart of Waihi,
        New Zealand.
        <br /><br />
        Andrew brings a background in precision manufacturing to every project — years
        spent building carbon fibre composite racing yachts and super-yachts, where
        tolerances are unforgiving and materials are trusted with a great deal riding
        on them.
        <br /><br />
        That same discipline now goes into framing — close attention to materials,
        proportion, and the quiet details that make a finished piece feel considered
        rather than assembled.
        <br /><br />
         In 2017, Andrew co-founded Waihi Beach Gallery with a former partner —
          and it was there, somewhat by serendipity and local demand, that he
          found his way into picture framing.
          <br /><br />
      </p>

      <div class="border-s-0 md:border-s border-brand-accent/10 mx-auto px-0 md:px-12">
        <p class="mt-4  text-stone-500 font-body leading-relaxed">
         
          In 2022 he moved on to start his own studio, Artifact Photo and Frame —
          the foundation of what is now Artifact Studio.
          <br /><br />
        </p>

        <p class="mt-4  text-stone-500 font-body leading-relaxed">
          That same curiosity hasn't slowed down. Alongside running the studio,
          Andrew is currently studying design at the University of Waikato — a
          deliberate choice to keep learning, and to bring new thinking back
          into the craft.
          <br /><br />
          Artifact Studio is the result: a small, considered practice built on precision,
          patience, and a genuine care for the things people bring in to be framed.
          <br /><br />
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>
